{{distinguish|Lolopo language}} {{Infobox language |name=Lipo |nativename=Lolopo, Lolongo |states=[[China]] |ethnicity=[[Lisu people|Lisu]] |speakers=250,000 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Lisoish languages|Lisoish]] |fam6=Lipo–Lolopo |script=[[Pollard script]] |iso3=lpo |glotto=lipo1242 |glottorefname=Lipo }}
'''Lipo''' (autonym: ''{{IPA|li˥pʰɔ˨˩}}''; {{zh|里泼}}), or '''Eastern Lisu''', is a language of the [[Lisu people]] of China, similar to but not intelligible with [[Lisu language|Lisu proper]]. Some Lipo are classified by the government as Lisu, others as [[Yi people|Yi]]. In some areas, the people prefer the name ''Lolopo'' or ''Lolongo''.
Some Lipo (''Lipa'' 利帕) speakers in Eryuan and Yongsheng counties are also referred to as ''Tujia'' (土家) (Yunnan 1956:19-20).<ref>Yunnan provincial ethnic classification research unit [云南省民族识别研究组]. 1956. ''Preliminary summary of ethnic classifications in Yunnan province: no. 1, 2'' [云南省民族识别研究第一、二阶段初步总结]. Beijing: Central University for Nationalities Research Institute 中央民族学院.</ref>
