{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox criminal | image = | image_name = | name = Nicole Baukus | image_size = | image_caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|4|02}} | birth_place = Houston, Texas, US | charge = | conviction = [[Manslaughter|Second degree vehicular manslaughter]] | conviction_penalty = 15 years | conviction_status = Inmate at [[Mountain View Unit]] in [[Gatesville, Texas]] }}
'''Nicole Nadra Baukus''' (born April 2, 1989) is an American woman convicted of two counts of vehicular manslaughter stemming from an accident on June 29, 2012 where she was driving intoxicated.<ref name=myfox>{{cite web|url=http://www.click2houston.com/news/surveillance-video-showed-during-wrongway-trial/21276424|title=Defense in wrong-way drunk driving trial of Nicole Baukus changes plea to guilty &#124; News - Home|publisher=click2houston.com|accessdate=2014-08-21}}</ref> Baukus pleaded guilty to the charges and was sentenced to 38 years in prison with the possibility of parole.<ref name=myfox/><ref name="chron">{{cite web|url=http://www.chron.com/news/houston-texas/houston/article/Wrong-way-driver-sentenced-to-38-years-in-prison-4704366.php|title=Wrong-way driver sentenced to 38 years in prison - Houston Chronicle|publisher=chron.com|accessdate=2014-08-21}}</ref> Highway surveillance cameras showed Baukus' vehicle traveling on the wrong side of [[Interstate 45]] after she had consumed alcohol at a nearby bar.<ref name= "Young woman charged">[http://www.khou.com/story/news/2014/07/20/11750554/ Young woman charged with DWI in I-45 wrong-way crash.] [[KHOU]], June 29, 2012</ref><ref name="yourhoustonnews">{{cite web|url=http://www.yourhoustonnews.com/courier/news/grand-jury-indicts-first-wrong-way-driver/article_228ad09b-a4cd-5cbb-b742-157232c9c080.html|title=Grand jury indicts first wrong-way driver - Your Houston News: News|publisher=yourhoustonnews.com|accessdate=2014-08-21}}</ref> A later request for a new trial was denied.<ref name="montgomerycountypolicereporter">{{cite web|url=http://montgomerycountypolicereporter.com/judge-denies-new-trial-wrong-way-driver/|title=judge denies new trial for wrong way driver - Montgomery County Police Reporter|publisher=montgomerycountypolicereporter.com|accessdate=2014-08-21}}</ref> Nicole Baukus attended and graduated from [[Oak Ridge High School (Montgomery County, Texas)|Oak Ridge High School]] in Conroe, Texas.
==Trial== Baukus was charged with two counts of second-degree felony intoxication manslaughter and one count of third-degree felony intoxication assault. After initially pleading not guilty to the charges against her, she pleaded guilty to two counts of vehicular manslaughter on August 1, 2013.<ref name=myfox/> Baukus was sentenced to a maximum of 15 years in prison on each count. She is currently eligible for parole in 2021. The judge in her trial, [[Micheal_T._Seiler|Michael Seiler]], resigned from the bench to avoid prosecution from matters unrelated to this case.<ref name= "Seiler Resigns">[http://www.chron.com/neighborhood/woodlands/news/article/Montgomery-County-judge-resigns-after-juror-flap-6834302.php Judge Micheale Seiler Resigns to Avoid Criminal Prosecution], February 16, 2016</ref>
==Appeal== Baukus filed an appeal of her conviction which was denied with a dissenting opinion in the Texas 9th District Court of Appeals. She filed a Petition for Discretionary Review with the Texas Court of Criminal Appeals which was refused. On September 11, 2017, Ms. Baukus filed a writ of habeas corpus in the 435th District Court of Montgomery County, Texas with allegations of police misconduct, planting of evidence, prosecutorial misconduct, and ineffective assistance of her trial lawyer. The case is now pending before the Texas Court of Criminal Appeals.
