{{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}} {{Infobox person | name =Rasool Ellore | birth_date ={{birth date and age|df=yes|1964|10|08}} | birth_place = [[Rajahmundry]], India | residence = [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]], Telangana, India | death_place = | birth_name = | website = | occupation = [[Cinematographer]] | title = [[Indian Society of Cinematographers|ISC]] | spouse = [[Jahnavi Ellore (anchor)|Jahnavi Ellore]] }}
'''Rasool Ellore Reddy''' (born 8 October 1964), also known as '''Rasool''', is an Indian [[cinematographer]], screenwriter, and director known for his works in [[Telugu cinema]], and [[bollywood]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.idlebrain.com/celeb/interview/rasoolellore.html|title=Rasool Ellore - Telugu Cinema interview - Telugu film cinematographer and director|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/familyentertainer-with-dollops-of-comedy/article5993882.ece|title=Family-entertainer with dollops of comedy|first=Suresh|last=Krishnamoorthy|publisher=}}</ref> He is the brother-in-law of noted cinematographer [[S. Gopal Reddy]]. He is known for his works in films such as ''[[Gaayam]]'', ''[[Gulabi (film)|Gulabi]]'', ''[[Chitram]]'', and others. He made his debut as a director with the [[romantic comedy]], ''[[Okariki Okaru]]''. He has garnered three state [[Nandi Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/2005/10/15/stories/2005101506760200.htm|title=The Hindu : Andhra Pradesh / Visakhapatnam News : All the action is for a bridge|first=|last=hynbu|publisher=}}</ref>
