'''United By Blue''' is a [[For-profit corporation|for-profit company]] based in [[Philadelphia]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://unitedbyblue.com/pages/our-mission|title=Our Mission|last=<!--no byline-->|first=|date=<!--no clear source date-->|website=United By Blue|publisher=United By Blue|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> It is an outdoor lifestyle brand that focuses on sustainable products including apparel, bags, and accessories.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nchannel.com/blog/united-by-blue-fulfillment-brand-growth/|title=United By Blue Founder/CEO Brian Linton Talks Fulfillment, Brand and Handling Growth|last=<!--no byline-->|first=|date=<!--no clear source date-->|website=United By Blue|publisher=Jillian Hufford|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=November 19, 2018}}</ref> It was founded by Brian Linton in 2010.<ref>{{cite news |title=What it’s really like being a small fish in big business pond |url=https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B_d8HD3Z8GFhdFJNMFR6b0JPaE9hVDJHZTNvN2ZnX1hCWklJ/view |accessdate=19 November 2018 |agency=The Philadelphia Inquirer |date=August 18, 2018 |page=E14}}</ref> The aim of United By Blue is to have rigorous standards of [[Social impact assessment|social]] and [[Environmental Performance Index|environmental performance]], accountability, and transparency.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harrison |first1=Kate |title=Small Businesses Can Benefit From Putting The Environment First |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kateharrison/2016/04/22/small-businesses-can-benefit-from-putting-the-environment-first/#5d46c02e4dff |website=Forbes |accessdate=19 November 2018}}</ref> It was certified as a [[B Corporation (certification)|B Corporation]] due to its meet on social sustainability and environmental performance standards, meet accountability standards, and to be transparent to the public according to the score it receive on the assessment by [[B Lab]]<ref name=":1" />.
